"Here's a medium-level Python problem for you:\n\n```json\n{\n    \"title\": \"Minimum Deletions to Make Array Sorted\",\n    \"description\": \"Given an array of integers, find the minimum number of deletions required to make the array sorted. A deletion at index i means removing the element at that index and all elements to its left from the array.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef min_deletions(arr: list[int)) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `arr` (list[int]): An array of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the minimum number of deletions required to make the array sorted.\\n\",\n    \"code\": \"\"\"\nimport heapq\n\ndef min_deletions(arr: list[int]) -> int:\n    heap = []\n    for num in arr:\n        heapq.heappush(heap, -num)\n    \n    deletions = 0\n    while len(heap) > 1:\n        a = -heapq.heappop(heap)\n        b = -heapq.heappop(heap)\n        if a < b:\n            heapq.heappush(heap, -(a + b))\n            deletions += 1\n    \n    return deletions\n\"\"\",\n    \"tests\": [\n        \"assert min_deletions([3, 2, 10, 5, 8]) == 4\",\n        \"assert min_deletions([-2, -3, 0, 6, 10, 7]) == 1\",\n        \"assert min_deletions([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) == 0\",\n        \"assert min_deletions([1, 3, 5]) == 2\"\n    ]\n}\n```"